description: Demolition of the existing buildings (with the exception of Kina House) and redevelopment of the site to deliver a mixed use development comprising 277 residential units and flexible commercial floorspace (Use Class A1-A4) at ground floor in buildings ranging from 2 to 15 storeys. The development also includes the re-provision of the St John Road Public Car Park, provision of residential car parking, cycle parking and servicing facilities and the refurbishment of Kina House at ground floor. This application is affecting the setting of East Ham Town Centre Conservation Area. This application is affecting the setting of Listed Buildings:- Public Library (Grade II), East Ham Town Hall (Grade II*), Former Fire Station (Grade II), Technical College (Grade II), Wall to East Ham Town Hall, Technical College and Library (Grade II), Fellowship House (Grade II), Police Station with Walls and Gatepiers to side (Grade II) and The Denmark Arms Public House (Grade II).
